summary:
This is my complete retexturing of the "Bathing Beauties or Beefcake - Luxury Suite" by Migal130
Now available in 2k, 1k and stock 0.5k resolutions.
New optional "Beefcake converter"
New optional "Classier Temple of Mara" (aka, the Wedding Hall)
New optional "BBLS Patio Furniture"
descriptionHtml:
[b][color=yellow]WARNING, Main files are for the new BBLS v 5.0 (or higher), GET IT FIRST![/color][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427[/url]

On a side note: If you like a mod, any mod, please come back to endorse it. Appreciation is a wonderfull motivator for modders.[/b]

[b][color=green]Introducing the NEW "A Classier BB Luxury Suite v 5.2"[/color][/b]
V5.2 is all about reduced texure file sizes (35%), and thusly improving performance.
No textures were changed nor reduced in resolution. These gains are from file optimization only.
Cleaned with Tes5Edit.
Note:
OMB was kind enough to rum some tests with Skyrim Performance Monitor for me. (Screenshots have been posted)
With "full" version the notable changes using v5.2 were.
-9% avg cpu use, -30% Disk I/O, -8% max memory useage, +1 avg FPS
This is not huge, but with the way some users are pushing thier systems to the limits, maybe it will help some folks out.
[img]http://static-1.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/19866-1-1365956590.jpg[/img]

[b][color=green]A New Optional file, BBLS Patio Furniture[/color][/b]
Featureing: "The Tikky Bar" w/ 3 NPC Staff, Lounge Chairs, Shade Umbrellas, A Player Useable Mead Keg (Free Mead just help yourself!), Towels & A Pool Raft.

[b][color=yellow]Required Files:[/color][/b]
"Bathing Beauties or Beefcake - Luxury Suite" by Migal130 [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427[/url]
"A Classier BB Luxury Suite by RIP88" (Main file of this page)
Summer Wear V2 nsfw [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/25237]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/25237[/url]
"ApachiiSkyHair_v_1_4_Full 0r 1_5_Full" [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/10168]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/10168[/url]
"ApachiiSkyHairFemale_v_1_2" [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/10168]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/10168[/url]
[b]Not Required, but fully supported[/b]
"Music and Dancing in the Luxury Suite" v2.0Beta [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/18462]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/18462[/url]
As always, available in "full" 2k objects + 4k clothes, "Light" 1k objects + 2k clothes, and "SuperLight" 0.5k objects + 2k clothes,
Please select the same Resolution as you currently use for Classier.
[b]Load Order[/b] This should load after classier and after Summerwear.
For a complete listing of the extended BBLS familys load order, read [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/articles/907/]BBLS (extended family) load order and you.[/url]
[b]Known Issues[/b]
The "bikini green" sold by the Tikky Bar girls, Is an error. They were never supposed to sell that item, it is a old test outfit from when the mod was in concept stages. I will NOT be releasing a fix for this, rather I will include this fix if/when any other changes get made.
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/19866-2-1360432184.jpg[/img]
[b]Additional credits for BBLS Patio Furniture[/b]
Voivod333, for allowing me to use assets from "Parasol WIP" [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/15807]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/15807[/url]
Snezko, for allowing me to use assets from "Bikini Clothes" [url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/6236]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/6236[/url]
(Snezkos extended credits, Cotyounoyume, the original mesh author)

[b][color=green]A New Optional file, Classier Temple of Mara[/color][/b]
Who wants to get married in a Temple that looks like a barn? Now your Wedding can be in a nicer looking place.
As always, available in "full" 2k res, "Light" 1k res, and "SuperLight" 0.5k res, Please select the same Resolution as you currently use for Classier.
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/19866-1-1354387944.jpg[/img]

[b][color=green]This is my complete retexturing of the "Bathing Beauties or Beefcake - Luxury Suite" by Migal130[/color][/b][url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427[/url]
(At his Request)
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/19866-1-1346141223.jpg[/img]

Now available in 2k, 1k and stock 0.5k resolutions!
It is JUST a retexturing, nothing else changes. All of BBLS's functionality remains untouched.
(It will Not overwrite anything vanilla) (It will Only change the textures of BBLS, nothing more.)

This all started when Migal130 told me how much he hated the floors. I decided to change them for him, and... well... you know, one thing led to another...
Almost everything has been retextured at this point.
I have a lot of time invested, and finnaly consider it finnished.

[b]"Migal says, I also use and highly recommend RIP88's impressive A Classier BB Luxury Suite'"[/b]

Planned additions:
Support for anything Migal chooses to add to the building in the future.

Change log:
v5.2
Contains assets of... "v5.0" and "v5.1" plus "BBLuxurySuiteClassierv5-0_DoorPatch" and the 5 "classier temple of mara" textures.
Reduced the file size of most textures, (35%) by optimizing file formats used. (no resolutions were reduced)
Improved door meshes for guard shack from "BBLuxurySuiteClassierv5-0_DoorPatch"
Cleaned esp with TesEdit.

V5.0 Everything listed in the unreleased v3, Plus support for everything Migel added in "BBLS v5"

v4.0 (skiped due to upcomeing changes in BBLS v5,
and my desire for people to easily tell they are installing compatable versions of "BBLS" and "Classier")

V3.0 (unreleased due to upcomeing changes in BBLS v5)
BBLS main house interior. (A few "new" textures and 1000little tweeks. Complete mesh overhaul for 2nd, 3rd floors, & ceilings.)
BBLS main house exterior. (I only changed the porch light back to normal, as apposed to red)
BBLS basement interior. (Added a few things to make it "better", but did not make it "classier")
BBLS basement "BOM's room" int. (Completely remade from scratch)

V 2.0
Made completely new textures at 2k resolution. (not all, but most)
Changed the textures on the building exterior.
Removed bookcase (for compatibility with BBLS4.0)

v 1.0
Initial release. (0.5k textures)

Required Files:
"Bathing Beauties or Beefcake - Luxury Suite" by Migal130[b](v5.0 or higher)[/b]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427]http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/11427[/url]

A very old vidio from v1.0
[youtube]eJf9I2xoAkA[/youtube]

Installation:
Extract the Contents of the "Data" folder to, your skyrimData directory, (typically, C:ProgramfilesSteamSteamAppscommonskyrimData)
Insure BBLuxurySuiteClassier.esp, Is turned on.

Uninstallation:
Remove;
BBLuxurySuiteClassier.esp, from skyrimData
everything from skyrimDatameshesarchitectureBBLS
everything from skyrimDatatexturesarchitectureBBLS
(there are NO original "BBLS" files in these 2 folders, so its safe to try this mod, and delete those 2 folders if you don't like it. )
My file structures are completely separate from "BBLS original".

Known Issues:
Insure that "BBLuxurySuiteClassier.esp" is the last of the "BBLuxurySuite"s in your load order.
Else you may find a stray rug or bookcase showing up, or doors missing the new textures, etc.

Incompatibilities:
Incompatible with "Enhanced Lights and FX" (ELFX overwrites 438 "stock meshes" fracturing them into many more "pieces" then the original mesh, thusly disrupting any mod that retextures these "stock meshes")

Incompatible with any mod that retextures the inside of "BBLS"
I don't really think there is another person crazy enough to do this, but it could happen.

Tools Used:
Photoshop
Nifscope
TESsnip
Creation Kit

Permissions:
Anyone is free to use anything that I have made for NON COMERCIAL use ONLY.
However, most of my work is based in some way off a stock Bethesda mesh or texture, so keep it in this game please.
Credits to those I have credited should be passed forward, of course. If using just parts, you can contact me for what credits should be passed on with what parts.

Nobody may upload my mod to any other sites, Repackage and claim it as their work, Profit from the use of "the mod in whole" or any of its assets, or restrict others from using ("their works" "based on my parts"). its just a game folks, lets keep it fun.

Credits:

deegola, for the Gothic Frame.3DS via http://www.turbosquid.com (free use)
Edward Burne-Jones, Fran√ßois Boucher, Nicolas Poussin, For their paintings via http://Art-Wallpaper.com (public domain)

Thanks To:
Quicksilver88, Rallynut88, Wifeofmigal, Urshi, Tikky, OldMansBeard (and assorted family members, who have been testing for weeks now.
The awesome modders ahead of me, without their work, I would not have had anything to dissect in my quest to learn all this.
